Text.SourceString: Well, hello… Nice to meet you. Call me <NPCName>Nina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, hello… Nice to meet you. Call me <NPCName>Nina</>.

Text.SourceString: What should I call you?
Text.LocalizedString: What should I call you?

Text.SourceString: Mother is always such a collector. I’m constantly finding new things around the house.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother is always such a collector. I’m constantly finding new things around the house.

Text.SourceString: I could sell the whole house, and I swear to you, new things would still keep popping up. Ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I could sell the whole house, and I swear to you, new things would still keep popping up. Ha!

Text.SourceString: I just adore this island. They call themselves “islanders.” Oh, my heart! So adorbs.
Text.LocalizedString: I just adore this island. They call themselves “islanders.” Oh, my heart! So adorbs.

Text.SourceString: The wild jackfruit is so sweet here. If you’re lucky, you might find some massive ones near the river.
Text.LocalizedString: The wild jackfruit is so sweet here. If you’re lucky, you might find some massive ones near the river.

Text.SourceString: Isn’t that spectacular?
Text.LocalizedString: Isn’t that spectacular?

Text.SourceString: If you see anything you like at the villa, just let me know, darl.//I can probably sell it to you.
Text.LocalizedString: If you see anything you like at the villa, just let me know, darl.//I can probably sell it to you.

Text.SourceString: I don’t need most of the things in my house.//It’d be best for me to rehome the art and the furniture, but it really isn’t that simple.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t need most of the things in my house.//It’d be best for me to rehome the art and the furniture, but it really isn’t that simple.

Text.SourceString: I’m heading to Dulca Island for the Autumn.//It’s the best time to visit, if you’re interested… Then I’m probably going to spend Winter with Mother.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m heading to Dulca Island for the Autumn.//It’s the best time to visit, if you’re interested… Then I’m probably going to spend Winter with Mother.

Text.SourceString: Oh yes, of course. They call it Fall here, not Autumn, don’t they?//<portrait=normal>It’s the falling leaves season.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yes, of course. They call it Fall here, not Autumn, don’t they?//<portrait=normal>It’s the falling leaves season.

Text.SourceString: I love the mayor. He’s like a father to me. Always makes sure I feel welcome here.//Like, who do you know with a better heart?
Text.LocalizedString: I love the mayor. He’s like a father to me. Always makes sure I feel welcome here.//Like, who do you know with a better heart?

Text.SourceString: No one, right?
Text.LocalizedString: No one, right?

Text.SourceString: This place is the best in Summer. Love, love, <Italic>love</> keeping up with my childhood friends!//<portrait=normal>Surfing, staying up, chilling at the beach. What more is there to life?
Text.LocalizedString: This place is the best in Summer. Love, love, <Italic>love</> keeping up with my childhood friends!//<portrait=normal>Surfing, staying up, chilling at the beach. What more is there to life?

Text.SourceString: Coral Island feels the most like home to me.//I feel like packing up and moving right back in this Winter!
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island feels the most like home to me.//I feel like packing up and moving right back in this Winter!

Text.SourceString: Is that impulsive? Maybe I should wait until Spring.//<portrait=annoyed>I need to talk to Mother about it first, anyway… See what she thinks.
Text.LocalizedString: Is that impulsive? Maybe I should wait until Spring.//<portrait=annoyed>I need to talk to Mother about it first, anyway… See what she thinks.

Text.SourceString: There's a vast collection of art and furniture in my home that I barely use.//<portrait=concerned>I'm considering finding them new homes, but it's not as easy as one might think.
Text.LocalizedString: There's a vast collection of art and furniture in my home that I barely use.//<portrait=concerned>I'm considering finding them new homes, but it's not as easy as one might think.

Text.SourceString: How are you doing today, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you doing today, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Remember, I’m rooting for you! Keep it up.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know what I’m rooting for just yet, but I am! Go <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Remember, I’m rooting for you! Keep it up.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know what I’m rooting for just yet, but I am! Go <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: I know Mother would tell me to do whatever makes me happy.//But I really don’t want to leave her alone, now that Father is gone.
Text.LocalizedString: I know Mother would tell me to do whatever makes me happy.//But I really don’t want to leave her alone, now that Father is gone.

Text.SourceString: I’m all she’s got. I feel bad, but I also don’t want to force her to move here with me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m all she’s got. I feel bad, but I also don’t want to force her to move here with me.

Text.SourceString: Oh my… I’m debating whether I should move back here this coming Winter or next year.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my… I’m debating whether I should move back here this coming Winter or next year.

Text.SourceString: Maybe next year. Start off with a clean slate, you know…
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe next year. Start off with a clean slate, you know…

Text.SourceString: I'm planning a day at the beach tomorrow, perhaps followed by a visit to the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>Will I see you there?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm planning a day at the beach tomorrow, perhaps followed by a visit to the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>Will I see you there?

Text.SourceString: No promises, though. If I get too exhausted, then I’ll just go straight home.
Text.LocalizedString: No promises, though. If I get too exhausted, then I’ll just go straight home.

Text.SourceString: You don’t look like a busy farmer, darling.//Everything’s okay at the farm, I hope?
Text.LocalizedString: You don’t look like a busy farmer, darling.//Everything’s okay at the farm, I hope?

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you something… Sometimes I feel like I’m being watched.//There’s an extra pair of eyes in the villa. I can feel it.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you something… Sometimes I feel like I’m being watched.//There’s an extra pair of eyes in the villa. I can feel it.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha… Never mind. I think I’ve been reading one too many mysteries.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha… Never mind. I think I’ve been reading one too many mysteries.

Text.SourceString: Falling asleep with my windows open is the best. The sound of the ocean is so relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: Falling asleep with my windows open is the best. The sound of the ocean is so relaxing.

Text.SourceString: You know, living alone isn’t as bad as I thought it would be.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, living alone isn’t as bad as I thought it would be.

Text.SourceString: Sure, occasionally you get lonely, but sometimes it’s nice to just be by yourself, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, occasionally you get lonely, but sometimes it’s nice to just be by yourself, you know?

Text.SourceString: I should host a dinner party and invite all my friends. Would you come?
Text.LocalizedString: I should host a dinner party and invite all my friends. Would you come?

Text.SourceString: My oh my! Darling, you have to come. There will be plenty of food and music… New friends!//<portrait=happy>It’ll be so much fun.
Text.LocalizedString: My oh my! Darling, you have to come. There will be plenty of food and music… New friends!//<portrait=happy>It’ll be so much fun.

Text.SourceString: I hate to call the villa a vacation home, because it’s actually home in my eyes… Not some resort hotel.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate to call the villa a vacation home, because it’s actually home in my eyes… Not some resort hotel.

Text.SourceString: My childhood friends are all here. This is where my parents had me.//Mother planted flowers in this soil. And Father…//<portrait=annoyed>And Father was laid to rest here.
Text.LocalizedString: My childhood friends are all here. This is where my parents had me.//Mother planted flowers in this soil. And Father…//<portrait=annoyed>And Father was laid to rest here.

Text.SourceString: For my seventh birthday, Father got me a small patch of land over on Turtle Island. Our family uses it for berry planting.
Text.LocalizedString: For my seventh birthday, Father got me a small patch of land over on Turtle Island. Our family uses it for berry planting.

Text.SourceString: Oh, nothing compared to your farm, doll! A blueberry to a watermelon! My patch of land is as small as my villa.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, nothing compared to your farm, doll! A blueberry to a watermelon! My patch of land is as small as my villa.

Text.SourceString: It’s strawberry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s strawberry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Text.SourceString: It’s blueberry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s blueberry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Text.SourceString: It’s cranberry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s cranberry season! Oh, I would love to visit a berry farm this time of year.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend the afternoon than toting around a basketful of berries and fresh flowers?

Text.SourceString: Living at the beach is hard to beat. Falling asleep with my windows open is simply the best.//The sound of the ocean is so relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: Living at the beach is hard to beat. Falling asleep with my windows open is simply the best.//The sound of the ocean is so relaxing.

Text.SourceString: Happy Sunday to you!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Sunday to you!

Text.SourceString: I get confused when people ask me where I’m from. Coral Island is definitely home to me, so I always tell them that.
Text.LocalizedString: I get confused when people ask me where I’m from. Coral Island is definitely home to me, so I always tell them that.

Text.SourceString: Even though I was born here, darling, Mother hails from an entirely different corner of the world.//Hence, the conundrum...am I truly a Coral Island native?
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I was born here, darling, Mother hails from an entirely different corner of the world.//Hence, the conundrum...am I truly a Coral Island native?

Text.SourceString: I must confess, there were times growing up when I felt as though I didn't quite match my own reflection in the family portrait.//An artist with mismatched paint, if you will.
Text.LocalizedString: I must confess, there were times growing up when I felt as though I didn't quite match my own reflection in the family portrait.//An artist with mismatched paint, if you will.

Text.SourceString: But over the years, I've learned that my unique blend is not a sign of not fitting in, but rather a badge of honor...a testament to the rich tapestry of my existence.//<portrait=happy>After all, what's life without a little spice?
Text.LocalizedString: But over the years, I've learned that my unique blend is not a sign of not fitting in, but rather a badge of honor...a testament to the rich tapestry of my existence.//<portrait=happy>After all, what's life without a little spice?

Text.SourceString: Growing up, I often felt like an amalgam of my parents, not quite mirroring either of them.//It made me feel somewhat out of place.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up, I often felt like an amalgam of my parents, not quite mirroring either of them.//It made me feel somewhat out of place.

Text.SourceString: Thankfully, none of the people here ever made me feel like my appearance matters too much.//Family gatherings, on the other hand... Let's just say my cousins had a knack for reminding me of my uniqueness.
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully, none of the people here ever made me feel like my appearance matters too much.//Family gatherings, on the other hand... Let's just say my cousins had a knack for reminding me of my uniqueness.

Text.SourceString: Being caught between two families, two cultures, has always lent a certain...intrigue to my life.//When I was with my mom's side, they would look at me and see Father.//With all the blondes, I was the only one with black hair.
Text.LocalizedString: Being caught between two families, two cultures, has always lent a certain...intrigue to my life.//When I was with my mom's side, they would look at me and see Father.//With all the blondes, I was the only one with black hair.

Text.SourceString: Then with Father's family, they would look at me and see Mother.//<portrait=normal>I was like her mirror in how I moved and behaved.
Text.LocalizedString: Then with Father's family, they would look at me and see Mother.//<portrait=normal>I was like her mirror in how I moved and behaved.

Text.SourceString: Spring cleaning is such a pain when you have a big house. It’s even worse when you have a mother who likes to buy so many things. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring cleaning is such a pain when you have a big house. It’s even worse when you have a mother who likes to buy so many things. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad it’s starting to get warmer. I was this close to packing up and moving somewhere else!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad it’s starting to get warmer. I was this close to packing up and moving somewhere else!

Text.SourceString: I’m so excited for Summer, darl. It’ll be so much fun!//<portrait=surprised>The food, the swimming, the beach – everything!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so excited for Summer, darl. It’ll be so much fun!//<portrait=surprised>The food, the swimming, the beach – everything!

Text.SourceString: I hate Spring cleaning.//<portrait=surprised>I should ask <NPCName>Suki</> to do it. She <Italic>loves</> Spring cleaning.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate Spring cleaning.//<portrait=surprised>I should ask <NPCName>Suki</> to do it. She <Italic>loves</> Spring cleaning.

Text.SourceString: I tried going into the ocean the other day, and it was still too cold!//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I need to wait a few more days…
Text.LocalizedString: I tried going into the ocean the other day, and it was still too cold!//<portrait=concerned>Maybe I need to wait a few more days…

Text.SourceString: Oh, darl, it’s finally, finally getting warmer. I can feel the Summer vibes just around the corner!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, darl, it’s finally, finally getting warmer. I can feel the Summer vibes just around the corner!

Text.SourceString: I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> is up to. Frantically cleaning the inn, probably.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> is up to. Frantically cleaning the inn, probably.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I need to tell you a funny story about <NPCName>Luke</>.//One time, we were hunting for ghosts by that temple near the villa. It was dark, and I sneaked away from him while he walked around the temple.//I hid, and when he noticed I was gone, he kept calling my name over and over again.//<portrait=surprised>So then, I jumped out and scared him! He fell down, and he cried and cried and cried!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I need to tell you a funny story about <NPCName>Luke</>.//One time, we were hunting for ghosts by that temple near the villa. It was dark, and I sneaked away from him while he walked around the temple.//I hid, and when he noticed I was gone, he kept calling my name over and over again.//<portrait=surprised>So then, I jumped out and scared him! He fell down, and he cried and cried and cried!

Text.SourceString: Can’t believe that crybaby grew up to be so tall.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t believe that crybaby grew up to be so tall.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Walter</> and Father used to take <NPCName>Luke</> and me sailing the first weekend of every Summer.//<portrait=sad>Eventually, we stopped that tradition, and then Father, well…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Walter</> and Father used to take <NPCName>Luke</> and me sailing the first weekend of every Summer.//<portrait=sad>Eventually, we stopped that tradition, and then Father, well…

Text.SourceString: Just look around us, darl. You can see why I always come back here in Summer, can’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: Just look around us, darl. You can see why I always come back here in Summer, can’t you?

Text.SourceString: When I was younger, we didn’t always live here. But Father always made sure we came here for Summer. It was his favorite place in the whole world.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was younger, we didn’t always live here. But Father always made sure we came here for Summer. It was his favorite place in the whole world.

Text.SourceString: Father was the one who taught me how to surf and sail. Well…not personally. He was too busy for that.//But he was the one pushing for lessons and camps.
Text.LocalizedString: Father was the one who taught me how to surf and sail. Well…not personally. He was too busy for that.//But he was the one pushing for lessons and camps.

Text.SourceString: The Beach Cleanup Festival is the main reason I love Summer so much.
Text.LocalizedString: The Beach Cleanup Festival is the main reason I love Summer so much.

Text.SourceString: When I was younger, Father and Mother took me to the beach almost every single day in Summer.//Father would play with me in the water, and Mother would make banana fritters.//<portrait=happy>We always finished the day with some corn on the cob from the cart. It was so much fun!
Text.LocalizedString: When I was younger, Father and Mother took me to the beach almost every single day in Summer.//Father would play with me in the water, and Mother would make banana fritters.//<portrait=happy>We always finished the day with some corn on the cob from the cart. It was so much fun!

Text.SourceString: Do you think <NPCName>Luke</> will still let me put flower crowns on him?//<portrait=normal>Probably not, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think <NPCName>Luke</> will still let me put flower crowns on him?//<portrait=normal>Probably not, huh?

Text.SourceString: Oh, do you happen to grow berries on your farm? I think Autumn is the perfect season for berry picking, don’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, do you happen to grow berries on your farm? I think Autumn is the perfect season for berry picking, don’t you?

Text.SourceString: I’m so <Italic>so</> sad Summer is over. Should I leave town again?//<portrait=happy>Just kidding! I think I’m gonna stay here for a while.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so <Italic>so</> sad Summer is over. Should I leave town again?//<portrait=happy>Just kidding! I think I’m gonna stay here for a while.

Text.SourceString: I forget how pretty Coral Island is in Autumn. It’s just so picturesque with all the falling leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: I forget how pretty Coral Island is in Autumn. It’s just so picturesque with all the falling leaves.

Text.SourceString: What do you call it, darl, Autumn or Fall?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you call it, darl, Autumn or Fall?

Text.SourceString: Around this time of the year, Mother always made sure we were ready for our annual skiing trip.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m not very good at it… It never really <Italic>hooked</> me, as it were.
Text.LocalizedString: Around this time of the year, Mother always made sure we were ready for our annual skiing trip.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m not very good at it… It never really <Italic>hooked</> me, as it were.

Text.SourceString: It’s getting cold, isn’t it?//<portrait=annoyed>Remind me again why I decided to move back here.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s getting cold, isn’t it?//<portrait=annoyed>Remind me again why I decided to move back here.

Text.SourceString: What should I do today?//The cold weather makes me lazy.
Text.LocalizedString: What should I do today?//The cold weather makes me lazy.

Text.SourceString: There’s something really beautiful about the beach in Winter, isn’t there?
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something really beautiful about the beach in Winter, isn’t there?

Text.SourceString: Oh, darling, how do you stay so active in Winter? It’s so cold!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, darling, how do you stay so active in Winter? It’s so cold!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival!//<portrait=normal>I definitely missed it when I moved away.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival!//<portrait=normal>I definitely missed it when I moved away.

Text.SourceString: We need to keep hydrated, always. Especially in Winter, when it’s dry like this.
Text.LocalizedString: We need to keep hydrated, always. Especially in Winter, when it’s dry like this.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Bree’s</> parties are always so much fun, aren’t they? Nowhere near as much fun as Mother’s, of course. Too bad you haven’t been to any.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Bree’s</> parties are always so much fun, aren’t they? Nowhere near as much fun as Mother’s, of course. Too bad you haven’t been to any.

Text.SourceString: I’m so tempted to spend the Winter somewhere warmer.//<portrait=happy>Want to join me sometime?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so tempted to spend the Winter somewhere warmer.//<portrait=happy>Want to join me sometime?

Text.SourceString: I’m not technically new here.//Oh no, no!//My family used to live on Coral Island until Mother decided to leave some time ago.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not technically new here.//Oh no, no!//My family used to live on Coral Island until Mother decided to leave some time ago.

Text.SourceString: Now I spend my Summers here, catching up with old friends…and making new ones along the way.
Text.LocalizedString: Now I spend my Summers here, catching up with old friends…and making new ones along the way.

Text.SourceString: I tried to get Mother to spend Summer here with me. Just this one time, you know. I didn’t want to come alone. But she refused.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to get Mother to spend Summer here with me. Just this one time, you know. I didn’t want to come alone. But she refused.

Text.SourceString: She prefers cold winds, she said. No use trying to talk Mother into anything. Fine by me…
Text.LocalizedString: She prefers cold winds, she said. No use trying to talk Mother into anything. Fine by me…

Text.SourceString: So, tell me. What have you learned about farming so far?
Text.LocalizedString: So, tell me. What have you learned about farming so far?

Text.SourceString: What a fun, simple life! I need to get me one of those. Oh, it’s just so tiring to always move from place to place, never feeling at home.
Text.LocalizedString: What a fun, simple life! I need to get me one of those. Oh, it’s just so tiring to always move from place to place, never feeling at home.

Text.SourceString: The villa is too big for me. But I know Mother would be outraged if I swapped it for a modest-sized cabin.
Text.LocalizedString: The villa is too big for me. But I know Mother would be outraged if I swapped it for a modest-sized cabin.

Text.SourceString: I could never, anyway. It’s my childhood home. There’s no way I could ever destroy or sell the villa.
Text.LocalizedString: I could never, anyway. It’s my childhood home. There’s no way I could ever destroy or sell the villa.

Text.SourceString: The villa is too big for me. But I know Mother would be outraged if I swapped it for a modest-sized cabin.
Text.LocalizedString: The villa is too big for me. But I know Mother would be outraged if I swapped it for a modest-sized cabin.

Text.SourceString: I could never, anyway. It’s my childhood home. There’s no way I could ever destroy or sell the villa.
Text.LocalizedString: I could never, anyway. It’s my childhood home. There’s no way I could ever destroy or sell the villa.

Text.SourceString: I’ll be here next Summer. Why wouldn’t I be? I’d miss it too much.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll be here next Summer. Why wouldn’t I be? I’d miss it too much.

Text.SourceString: It would be such fun to stay for Autumn! But I can’t… Ugh!
Text.LocalizedString: It would be such fun to stay for Autumn! But I can’t… Ugh!

Text.SourceString: I need to pack tomorrow. I’m bringing back some antiques and wine for Mother.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to pack tomorrow. I’m bringing back some antiques and wine for Mother.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! What a fun Summer! I just absolutely love it here.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! What a fun Summer! I just absolutely love it here.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the wind is nice and breezy today!
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the wind is nice and breezy today!

Text.SourceString: We got just what we needed.
Text.LocalizedString: We got just what we needed.

Text.SourceString: This may sound a bit silly, but I’m curious about the forest. I heard there are monsters in the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: This may sound a bit silly, but I’m curious about the forest. I heard there are monsters in the cavern.

Text.SourceString: I’m afraid if I go to the forest alone, I might get lost and run into one of those monsters.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m afraid if I go to the forest alone, I might get lost and run into one of those monsters.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha ha. Silly, I know.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha ha. Silly, I know.

Text.SourceString: The leaves are solid brown now. It’s a sign the trees will start losing leaves soon.
Text.LocalizedString: The leaves are solid brown now. It’s a sign the trees will start losing leaves soon.

Text.SourceString: The weather has definitely changed, but not enough to need a sweater.//I’m fine, thanks for asking.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather has definitely changed, but not enough to need a sweater.//I’m fine, thanks for asking.

Text.SourceString: I got my party-planning gene from Mother.//She’d invite everybody on the island for my birthday.
Text.LocalizedString: I got my party-planning gene from Mother.//She’d invite everybody on the island for my birthday.

Text.SourceString: I never really understood why, because honestly, to me, it was more tiring than anything. And I always had to wear some itchy dress. I hated those. The parties, though – They were out of this world.
Text.LocalizedString: I never really understood why, because honestly, to me, it was more tiring than anything. And I always had to wear some itchy dress. I hated those. The parties, though – They were out of this world.

Text.SourceString: Oh, how I miss the sound of waves! I just spend the day curled up under a blanket.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, how I miss the sound of waves! I just spend the day curled up under a blanket.

Text.SourceString: Mother always insisted we go skiing in Winter, because you can do everything else any other time, according to her.//But skiing can only be done in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother always insisted we go skiing in Winter, because you can do everything else any other time, according to her.//But skiing can only be done in Winter.

Text.SourceString: She’s not wrong, but it doesn’t make it right. I mean, every Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>? Skiing? Come on!
Text.LocalizedString: She’s not wrong, but it doesn’t make it right. I mean, every Winter, <PlayerName>$player</>? Skiing? Come on!

Text.SourceString: The one time I’m here, it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: The one time I’m here, it rains.

Text.SourceString: The one time I’m here, it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: The one time I’m here, it rains.

Text.SourceString: Your boots are soaked! It must be raining hard outside, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Your boots are soaked! It must be raining hard outside, huh?

Text.SourceString: Humph. Oh well… It’s only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy?
Text.LocalizedString: Humph. Oh well… It’s only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy?

Text.SourceString: The one time I’m here, it rains like this.
Text.LocalizedString: The one time I’m here, it rains like this.

Text.SourceString: Bad luck, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: Bad luck, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! Was that thunder I just heard?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! Was that thunder I just heard?

Text.SourceString: Humph. Oh well… The rain is only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy and thundery?
Text.LocalizedString: Humph. Oh well… The rain is only water, right? So what if it’s a little muddy and thundery?

Text.SourceString: Oh, this rain isn’t going to stop me from leaving my house.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, this rain isn’t going to stop me from leaving my house.

Text.SourceString: It’s just a little bit of water.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s just a little bit of water.

Text.SourceString: This place hasn’t changed. I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: This place hasn’t changed. I love it.

Text.SourceString: Father used to bring me here after hours to get a treat.
Text.LocalizedString: Father used to bring me here after hours to get a treat.

Text.SourceString: I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I’ll always belong here…
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I’ll always belong here…

Text.SourceString: Close to Father.
Text.LocalizedString: Close to Father.

Text.SourceString: My dad worked long hours at home, and there was a period when he didn’t come out of his office for days at a time.
Text.LocalizedString: My dad worked long hours at home, and there was a period when he didn’t come out of his office for days at a time.

Text.SourceString: It was a really bad habit of his… Overworking himself. Then he would bring me here for father-daughter time to make up for the time he spent working.
Text.LocalizedString: It was a really bad habit of his… Overworking himself. Then he would bring me here for father-daughter time to make up for the time he spent working.

Text.SourceString: Did I really call him Dad? Ha! That’s new.
Text.LocalizedString: Did I really call him Dad? Ha! That’s new.

Text.SourceString: You come here to dance, don’t you? You look like the dancing type.
Text.LocalizedString: You come here to dance, don’t you? You look like the dancing type.

Text.SourceString: Come on! Show me what you’ve got.
Text.LocalizedString: Come on! Show me what you’ve got.

Text.SourceString: Father would flip if he knew I cut my hair short like this!
Text.LocalizedString: Father would flip if he knew I cut my hair short like this!

Text.SourceString: Ha! Kidding. He wouldn’t! Father wouldn’t care. He would literally let me do whatever I wanted… And I did.//Mother was angry every time I threw dinner plates across the table. But not Father.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha! Kidding. He wouldn’t! Father wouldn’t care. He would literally let me do whatever I wanted… And I did.//Mother was angry every time I threw dinner plates across the table. But not Father.

Text.SourceString: “Helena, she’s just a child. It’s just a plate. We still have plenty.” Blah, blah, blah.//A monster, I was.
Text.LocalizedString: “Helena, she’s just a child. It’s just a plate. We still have plenty.” Blah, blah, blah.//A monster, I was.

Text.SourceString: This volleyball court wasn’t here last year. I wonder if this was Pufferfish’s doing as well.
Text.LocalizedString: This volleyball court wasn’t here last year. I wonder if this was Pufferfish’s doing as well.

Text.SourceString: Up for a game of volleyball?
Text.LocalizedString: Up for a game of volleyball?

Text.SourceString: I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I’ll always belong here…
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose it doesn’t matter how far away I go. I’ll always belong here…

Text.SourceString: Close to Father.
Text.LocalizedString: Close to Father.

Text.SourceString: I don’t see kids building elaborate sandcastles anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t see kids building elaborate sandcastles anymore.

Text.SourceString: I suppose it may be a different era now.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose it may be a different era now.

Text.SourceString: Wait, are you joking? You don’t know how to sail?
Text.LocalizedString: Wait, are you joking? You don’t know how to sail?

Text.SourceString: So, when you were in school, what did you do during your Summer breaks, if not sailing?
Text.LocalizedString: So, when you were in school, what did you do during your Summer breaks, if not sailing?

Text.SourceString: I’d invite you in, but the house still smells a bit musty.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d invite you in, but the house still smells a bit musty.

Text.SourceString: Maybe next time…
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe next time…

Text.SourceString: It’s great to be back.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s great to be back.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t spent a Winter here in so long.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t spent a Winter here in so long.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh, I hope the heat still works.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh, I hope the heat still works.

Text.SourceString: I don’t need most of the things here. My family has so much unnecessary stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t need most of the things here. My family has so much unnecessary stuff.

Text.SourceString: This stuff is never used. It’s probably bored, sitting around with nobody paying attention to it.
Text.LocalizedString: This stuff is never used. It’s probably bored, sitting around with nobody paying attention to it.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I rarely spend my days at home.//The whole living alone thing gets boring fast, so I come here instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I rarely spend my days at home.//The whole living alone thing gets boring fast, so I come here instead.

Text.SourceString: You know how it is, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re all alone on that farm too.//<portrait=annoyed>Or do you have company?
Text.LocalizedString: You know how it is, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re all alone on that farm too.//<portrait=annoyed>Or do you have company?

Text.SourceString: I learned to sail a long time ago, when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Father sent me to a Summer camp where I also learned to scuba dive.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned to sail a long time ago, when I was <NPCName>Valentina’s</> age. Father sent me to a Summer camp where I also learned to scuba dive.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a big diver, but it did add some heft to my college application.//And it comes in handy for conversation at cocktail parties. So, I’m grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a big diver, but it did add some heft to my college application.//And it comes in handy for conversation at cocktail parties. So, I’m grateful.

Text.SourceString: Wait, are you joking? You don’t know how to sail?
Text.LocalizedString: Wait, are you joking? You don’t know how to sail?

Text.SourceString: So, when you were in school, what did you do during your Summer breaks, if not sailing?
Text.LocalizedString: So, when you were in school, what did you do during your Summer breaks, if not sailing?

Text.SourceString: We always have so much fun together. Did you notice that?
Text.LocalizedString: We always have so much fun together. Did you notice that?

Text.SourceString: It’s like we’re good friends or something.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s like we’re good friends or something.

Text.SourceString: This town is like a cute little time capsule.//Hasn’t changed much since I left. Without a doubt, it carries a lot of memories.
Text.LocalizedString: This town is like a cute little time capsule.//Hasn’t changed much since I left. Without a doubt, it carries a lot of memories.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Carries some bad memories too, though.//So, not a very cute time capsule, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Carries some bad memories too, though.//So, not a very cute time capsule, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Lily</> is a dear friend. She stays at the villa when I’m away. If you want to win brownie points with her, give her omurice.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Lily</> is a dear friend. She stays at the villa when I’m away. If you want to win brownie points with her, give her omurice.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell her I told you that. Take the credit!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell her I told you that. Take the credit!

Text.SourceString: Am I really? A smart person? Well, takes one to know one.//I always enjoy my conversations with you, precisely because of that.
Text.LocalizedString: Am I really? A smart person? Well, takes one to know one.//I always enjoy my conversations with you, precisely because of that.

Text.SourceString: You seem to always have smart insights into things.//You have broad knowledge, I noticed.
Text.LocalizedString: You seem to always have smart insights into things.//You have broad knowledge, I noticed.

Text.SourceString: My parents collected antiques from different eras.//That’s how they bonded. Over old, musty decor. Shocking!
Text.LocalizedString: My parents collected antiques from different eras.//That’s how they bonded. Over old, musty decor. Shocking!

Text.SourceString: Who am I kidding? I love it too! I love old, musty decor. Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: Who am I kidding? I love it too! I love old, musty decor. Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: My family used to pay some local farmers, Mr. and Mrs. Dudley, to look after the farm with Mother.//Back when she was still healthy…
Text.LocalizedString: My family used to pay some local farmers, Mr. and Mrs. Dudley, to look after the farm with Mother.//Back when she was still healthy…

Text.SourceString: We built the cabin for them to live in, and they kept most of what they earned from the harvest.
Text.LocalizedString: We built the cabin for them to live in, and they kept most of what they earned from the harvest.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad your grandparents purchased the farm from my parents.//Because if it weren’t for that… I may never have met you.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad your grandparents purchased the farm from my parents.//Because if it weren’t for that… I may never have met you.

Text.SourceString: That farm has the history of both our families in it.//<portrait=happy>It would be interesting to see what it would be like to live there…together.
Text.LocalizedString: That farm has the history of both our families in it.//<portrait=happy>It would be interesting to see what it would be like to live there…together.

Text.SourceString: Mr. and Mrs. Dudley don’t work for us anymore. They retired and moved to Beluga Bay.
Text.LocalizedString: Mr. and Mrs. Dudley don’t work for us anymore. They retired and moved to Beluga Bay.

Text.SourceString: Mother was getting too sick to care for the garden.//Father wasn’t in great condition either… It was for the best.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother was getting too sick to care for the garden.//Father wasn’t in great condition either… It was for the best.

Text.SourceString: Father gave the farm to Mother as a birthday or anniversary gift. I can’t remember which.//<portrait=normal>But at that point, they were fighting a lot, and she thought it was just Father’s way to shut her up.
Text.LocalizedString: Father gave the farm to Mother as a birthday or anniversary gift. I can’t remember which.//<portrait=normal>But at that point, they were fighting a lot, and she thought it was just Father’s way to shut her up.

Text.SourceString: He was acting very distant, and Mother kept complaining about us never having family dinners anymore.//<portrait=annoyed>It was a mess.
Text.LocalizedString: He was acting very distant, and Mother kept complaining about us never having family dinners anymore.//<portrait=annoyed>It was a mess.

Text.SourceString: When Mother was still walking well, and she could work, she enjoyed being on that farm. Being in the sun.//It was good to see.
Text.LocalizedString: When Mother was still walking well, and she could work, she enjoyed being on that farm. Being in the sun.//It was good to see.

Text.SourceString: Father was a thoughtful man.//He loved her very much.
Text.LocalizedString: Father was a thoughtful man.//He loved her very much.

Text.SourceString: Am I interested in anyone here?//Hmm… No. Not really.
Text.LocalizedString: Am I interested in anyone here?//Hmm… No. Not really.

Text.SourceString: Let me take that back… There is one person, actually.//A very smart, <Italic>very</> flirty person who piques my interest.//<portrait=happy>Not telling you who…
Text.LocalizedString: Let me take that back… There is one person, actually.//A very smart, <Italic>very</> flirty person who piques my interest.//<portrait=happy>Not telling you who…

Text.SourceString: I hate to monopolize our conversations. So, please, just stop me when you’ve had enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate to monopolize our conversations. So, please, just stop me when you’ve had enough.

Text.SourceString: The truth is…it’s hard for me to think clearly when I’m around you.
Text.LocalizedString: The truth is…it’s hard for me to think clearly when I’m around you.

Text.SourceString: Soon after Father passed away, Mother decided to move our whole life out of here.//She hasn’t returned since.
Text.LocalizedString: Soon after Father passed away, Mother decided to move our whole life out of here.//She hasn’t returned since.

Text.SourceString: Not to check on the villa, not to visit Father’s grave… Never.//Sometimes, she and <NPCName>Bree</> have lunch together, but never on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: Not to check on the villa, not to visit Father’s grave… Never.//Sometimes, she and <NPCName>Bree</> have lunch together, but never on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: I asked Mother why she never wanted to visit Coral Island. Oh yeah, I did!//She just brushed it off, saying she’d been here her whole adult life, and she’d had enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked Mother why she never wanted to visit Coral Island. Oh yeah, I did!//She just brushed it off, saying she’d been here her whole adult life, and she’d had enough.

Text.SourceString: I guess now we know where I got my dramatic gene. Heh!
Text.LocalizedString: I guess now we know where I got my dramatic gene. Heh!

Text.SourceString: Before moving back to Coral Island, I decided it was time for Mother and me to clean up our stuff here.//Then I came here that Summer to pick up some of my antiques and check out the new farmer.
Text.LocalizedString: Before moving back to Coral Island, I decided it was time for Mother and me to clean up our stuff here.//Then I came here that Summer to pick up some of my antiques and check out the new farmer.

Text.SourceString: I was shocked – amazed – to meet you. You’re so cute.//Took my breath away.
Text.LocalizedString: I was shocked – amazed – to meet you. You’re so cute.//Took my breath away.

Text.SourceString: Father was a good man, <PlayerName>$player</>. But there was a period…umm…toward the end of his life, when he was distant from us.//He got skinnier and skinnier.
Text.LocalizedString: Father was a good man, <PlayerName>$player</>. But there was a period…umm…toward the end of his life, when he was distant from us.//He got skinnier and skinnier.

Text.SourceString: He was so small when he…//We never knew what was wrong with him. Doctors said there was nothing wrong.//<portrait=sad>All the tests were negative. It was heartbreaking to see him that way. Mother and I – we never got our answers.
Text.LocalizedString: He was so small when he…//We never knew what was wrong with him. Doctors said there was nothing wrong.//<portrait=sad>All the tests were negative. It was heartbreaking to see him that way. Mother and I – we never got our answers.

Text.SourceString: Oh dear… Thank you. You’re such a flirt.//<portrait=blushing>You don’t look bad yourself. You obviously know that… People must throw themselves at you. I kind of hate it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh dear… Thank you. You’re such a flirt.//<portrait=blushing>You don’t look bad yourself. You obviously know that… People must throw themselves at you. I kind of hate it.

Text.SourceString: Stop it, you… I just threw something on. Nothing fancy at all.//If you keep complimenting me, I’ll have to put you in my pocket and take you home with me.
Text.LocalizedString: Stop it, you… I just threw something on. Nothing fancy at all.//If you keep complimenting me, I’ll have to put you in my pocket and take you home with me.

Text.SourceString: My head has gotten so large since I met you. The compliments… They’re gonna get to me, you know.//<portrait=happy>And you do <Italic>not</> want to see the consequences.
Text.LocalizedString: My head has gotten so large since I met you. The compliments… They’re gonna get to me, you know.//<portrait=happy>And you do <Italic>not</> want to see the consequences.

Text.SourceString: Mother likes to garden. She used to only plant flowers, but sometimes she planted berries for us to harvest during berry season, like now.
Text.LocalizedString: Mother likes to garden. She used to only plant flowers, but sometimes she planted berries for us to harvest during berry season, like now.

Text.SourceString: My parents and I would make a day of it.//<portrait=normal>Father would take a day off from his banking job. Just go to the farm, bring some lunch, and harvest all kinds of berries.//Blueberries, blackberries…
Text.LocalizedString: My parents and I would make a day of it.//<portrait=normal>Father would take a day off from his banking job. Just go to the farm, bring some lunch, and harvest all kinds of berries.//Blueberries, blackberries…

Text.SourceString: People are getting creative with stories nowadays. I don’t pay attention to gossip, darl.//I don’t care what people say about why my family left the island.
Text.LocalizedString: People are getting creative with stories nowadays. I don’t pay attention to gossip, darl.//I don’t care what people say about why my family left the island.

Text.SourceString: I’ve heard plenty of theories myself – about my own family.//<portrait=normal>The most absurd one was that Father died from some black magic, and now whatever it was is after Mother. They say that’s why Mother was so “scared” to come back here.//<portrait=annoyed>Foolish! An insensitive take on a tragedy.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve heard plenty of theories myself – about my own family.//<portrait=normal>The most absurd one was that Father died from some black magic, and now whatever it was is after Mother. They say that’s why Mother was so “scared” to come back here.//<portrait=annoyed>Foolish! An insensitive take on a tragedy.

Text.SourceString: I live way too far from your place. Ugh.//Don’t let it stop you from visiting me, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I live way too far from your place. Ugh.//Don’t let it stop you from visiting me, though.

Text.SourceString: If you get tired, you’re welcome to stay the night. There are extra bedrooms…if you’ll be needing one.
Text.LocalizedString: If you get tired, you’re welcome to stay the night. There are extra bedrooms…if you’ll be needing one.

Text.SourceString: I get why people like this place.//It’s so homey here…
Text.LocalizedString: I get why people like this place.//It’s so homey here…

Text.SourceString: The family that used to take care of the farm for us always had the same dinner here, for years.
Text.LocalizedString: The family that used to take care of the farm for us always had the same dinner here, for years.

Text.SourceString: In retrospect, I probably wouldn’t have moved back if this island were overrun with drilling sites.//Why would anyone?
Text.LocalizedString: In retrospect, I probably wouldn’t have moved back if this island were overrun with drilling sites.//Why would anyone?

Text.SourceString: Father and I used to sit there, right there near the pool table.//Those are the exact stools Father and I used to sit our <Italic>butts</> on.
Text.LocalizedString: Father and I used to sit there, right there near the pool table.//Those are the exact stools Father and I used to sit our <Italic>butts</> on.

Text.SourceString: I can’t remember if I turned my TV off before coming here.//Yeah, I did.//Wait… No… Never mind.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should call it a night. Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t remember if I turned my TV off before coming here.//Yeah, I did.//Wait… No… Never mind.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should call it a night. Yeah.

Text.SourceString: What do you think about this house?//Do you like it? Should I repaint the walls?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think about this house?//Do you like it? Should I repaint the walls?

Text.SourceString: The flowers here are beautiful. It makes me feel like a fairy when I’m in this garden.
Text.LocalizedString: The flowers here are beautiful. It makes me feel like a fairy when I’m in this garden.

Text.SourceString: I spoke to <NpcName>Raj</> the other day.//They sure know a lot about coffee. I don’t think I understood half the things they said.
Text.LocalizedString: I spoke to <NpcName>Raj</> the other day.//They sure know a lot about coffee. I don’t think I understood half the things they said.

Text.SourceString: I’ve always tried to make it to every festival, even when I didn’t live here.//They’re too precious to miss!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve always tried to make it to every festival, even when I didn’t live here.//They’re too precious to miss!

Text.SourceString: That’s one of the advantages of having a house here. You can just pop in anytime and stay for the night.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s one of the advantages of having a house here. You can just pop in anytime and stay for the night.

Text.SourceString: I miss farming with Mother, waking up early and strolling around rows and rows of flowers.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss farming with Mother, waking up early and strolling around rows and rows of flowers.

Text.SourceString: I have a lot of beautiful memories here.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a lot of beautiful memories here.

Text.SourceString: Care to join us, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//I'm just out here soaking up the sun.
Text.LocalizedString: Care to join us, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//I'm just out here soaking up the sun.

Text.SourceString: It’s a bit too cold to keep the windows open now.//<portrait=concerned>The ocean wind is strong.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a bit too cold to keep the windows open now.//<portrait=concerned>The ocean wind is strong.
